1
00:00:11,429 --> 00:00:14,390
♪ We face the music together ♪

2
00:00:15,766 --> 00:00:19,103
♪ And throw our hats
in the ring ♪

3
00:00:22,356 --> 00:00:25,276
♪ Facing all kinds of weather ♪

4
00:00:27,403 --> 00:00:30,989
♪ And not afraid of anything ♪

5
00:00:30,990 --> 00:00:33,074
♪ Hey ♪

6
00:00:33,075 --> 00:00:35,869
♪ When the sun comes up,
we'll be on our way ♪

7
00:00:35,870 --> 00:00:38,163
♪ And we don't care
where we land ♪

8
00:00:38,164 --> 00:00:40,915
♪ And the waves are high,
but we won't turn round ♪

9
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:44,711
♪ 'Cause your hand
is in my hand ♪

10
00:00:44,712 --> 00:00:46,671
♪ And, oh-oh ♪

11
00:00:46,672 --> 00:00:50,467
♪ You make me feel invincible ♪

12
00:00:50,468 --> 00:00:53,386
♪ 'Cause it's you and me ♪

13
00:00:53,387 --> 00:00:56,723
♪ Through the wind and hail ♪

14
00:00:56,724 --> 00:01:01,312
♪ Setting sail into the world ♪♪

15
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:10,236
I mean, look, even if you're
a total noob at investing,

16
00:01:10,237 --> 00:01:12,322
you'll still reap more
with the 30-year mortgage.

17
00:01:12,323 --> 00:01:13,740
Good to know.

18
00:01:13,741 --> 00:01:15,325
It's such a great house.

19
00:01:15,326 --> 00:01:17,619
Thanks. Of course,
you'll qualify

20
00:01:17,620 --> 00:01:19,579
for a VA loan,
you lucky son of a gun.

21
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:22,123
Sounds like a pretty fair trade

22
00:01:22,124 --> 00:01:24,375
for risking his life
for his country.

23
00:01:24,376 --> 00:01:29,047
So, uh, you ever killed anyone?

24
00:01:29,048 --> 00:01:31,132
Well, Nick,
my first time downrange,

25
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:32,675
I started as a gunner in Ramadi.

26
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:35,553
After BRC, I got deployed
with 1st Recon

27
00:01:35,554 --> 00:01:37,764
to find a terror cell so
deeply embedded with civilians

28
00:01:37,765 --> 00:01:39,349
that we couldn't
tell the difference,

29
00:01:39,350 --> 00:01:41,768
so what do you think?

30
00:01:41,769 --> 00:01:42,853
Excuse us.

31
00:01:44,897 --> 00:01:46,523
Was that really necessary?

32
00:01:46,524 --> 00:01:48,733
Who asks that to somebody
they just met?

33
00:01:48,734 --> 00:01:50,902
Oh.

34
00:01:50,903 --> 00:01:52,070
You ready to head out?

35
00:01:52,071 --> 00:01:53,655
Spence, it's not even dark.

36
00:01:53,656 --> 00:01:55,490
The plan was to stay an hour.

37
00:01:55,491 --> 00:01:56,616
We can't miss the fireworks.

38
00:01:56,617 --> 00:01:57,742
I'll look bad
in front of my boss.

39
00:01:57,743 --> 00:01:59,702
All right, sundown's
at 2100 hours.

40
00:01:59,703 --> 00:02:01,538
Leave at 2120?

41
00:02:01,539 --> 00:02:03,623
Fine.

42
00:02:03,624 --> 00:02:05,875
Uh, the kids are out
of sparklers,

43
00:02:05,876 --> 00:02:07,502
so I'm gonna make
a quick run with Nick.

44
00:02:07,503 --> 00:02:08,920
I'll go with you.

45
00:02:08,921 --> 00:02:11,632
I'll be five minutes. Okay?

46
00:02:25,354 --> 00:02:27,356
[garbled radio transmission]

47
00:02:28,524 --> 00:02:31,192
[bomb whistling]

48
00:02:31,193 --> 00:02:34,195
Coming in. Clear.
Right perimeter clear.

49
00:02:34,196 --> 00:02:36,698
Is left perimeter clear?

50
00:02:36,699 --> 00:02:38,533
Left perimeter clear.

51
00:02:38,534 --> 00:02:40,618
- Get him out! Get him out!
- Hey! What the hell?!

52
00:02:40,619 --> 00:02:42,370
Quick time!

53
00:02:42,371 --> 00:02:44,539
[Spence] You don't need
more sparklers.

54
00:02:44,540 --> 00:02:46,082
There's plenty back there.

55
00:02:46,083 --> 00:02:49,335
Thank you, baby.
You're so sweet.

56
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:51,338
I love you.

57
00:02:52,548 --> 00:02:54,550
[rock music playing quietly]

58
00:02:58,304 --> 00:03:00,306
♪ ♪

59
00:03:02,474 --> 00:03:04,435
[hissing]

60
00:03:09,106 --> 00:03:11,482
I think it's been
going on for a while.

61
00:03:11,483 --> 00:03:13,610
Between my husband
and your wife.

62
00:03:13,611 --> 00:03:16,571
- My wife wouldn't do that.
- Why not?

63
00:03:16,572 --> 00:03:18,448
Because that's not
part of the plan.

64
00:03:18,449 --> 00:03:20,742
[loud firework explodes]

65
00:03:20,743 --> 00:03:25,622
Believe what you like, but...

66
00:03:25,623 --> 00:03:28,458
I'm declaring July 5th
my Independence Day.

67
00:03:28,459 --> 00:03:30,461
[fireworks popping, squealing]

68
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:38,719
Babe, have you seen my phone?

69
00:03:42,348 --> 00:03:44,350
Can you call it?

70
00:03:46,644 --> 00:03:49,271
- [phone ringing]
- [dog barking]

71
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:55,945
[phone continues ringing]

72
00:03:57,071 --> 00:03:59,072
Uh...

73
00:03:59,073 --> 00:04:02,910
why is my phone
in Charlie's dirty diaper?

74
00:04:03,953 --> 00:04:05,703
That's a good question.

75
00:04:05,704 --> 00:04:08,498
And I could ask you why
you put your other mobile device

76
00:04:08,499 --> 00:04:10,708
in places it doesn't belong.

77
00:04:10,709 --> 00:04:12,919
Now...

78
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:15,673
tell me the truth.

79
00:04:16,757 --> 00:04:19,300
[sighs]

80
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:21,511
At least he admitted the affair.

81
00:04:21,512 --> 00:04:24,347
He didn't have a choice.

82
00:04:24,348 --> 00:04:26,766
- [Nick] Every day. Every day.
- [Charlie crying]

83
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:30,312
Yes, he's awake.
I can't believe you woke him.

84
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:34,607
[Alison] What happened next?

85
00:04:34,608 --> 00:04:36,943
[Isabelle] I said
all my worst fears.

86
00:04:36,944 --> 00:04:39,696
That we'd still be doing great
if I hadn't gotten pregnant.

87
00:04:39,697 --> 00:04:43,408
But a baby reminds Nick
that he's not young anymore,

88
00:04:43,409 --> 00:04:46,411
and he can't handle
the responsibility.

89
00:04:46,412 --> 00:04:49,205
Sometimes you throw
accusations out

90
00:04:49,206 --> 00:04:51,749
that you want someone to deny.

91
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:54,043
And then they don't.

92
00:04:54,044 --> 00:04:55,712
[Charlie cooing]

93
00:04:55,713 --> 00:04:57,964
[Alison] So what do you want?

94
00:04:57,965 --> 00:04:59,967
I'm...

95
00:05:02,594 --> 00:05:05,138
I'm very tired.

96
00:05:05,139 --> 00:05:07,974
- I need a teammate.
- [Alison exhales]

97
00:05:07,975 --> 00:05:12,563
Well, it sounds like
you have more to work through.

98
00:05:19,069 --> 00:05:22,823
[man and woman grunting
in video game]

99
00:05:23,866 --> 00:05:25,742
Yeah!

100
00:05:25,743 --> 00:05:27,827
- [grunting continues]
- [phone chimes]

101
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:29,830
♪ ♪

102
00:05:38,464 --> 00:05:41,674
Jeannie, can we talk?

103
00:05:41,675 --> 00:05:44,135
The last time we talked,
it didn't go so well.

104
00:05:44,136 --> 00:05:45,887
Can't you understand why?

105
00:05:45,888 --> 00:05:47,722
At this point, I don't know

106
00:05:47,723 --> 00:05:49,348
what else there is to say.

107
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:51,684
I saw you went back
to your maiden name on Facebook.

108
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:53,687
[grunting]

109
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:59,317
Are you gonna leave me
another angry voice message?

110
00:05:59,318 --> 00:06:00,985
Does that make you feel better?

111
00:06:00,986 --> 00:06:04,031
[yelling]

112
00:06:08,869 --> 00:06:10,870
Nothing makes me feel better.

113
00:06:10,871 --> 00:06:14,792
Spence, sign the damn papers.

114
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:22,799
[woman on phone] Sit tight,
Mr. Boyles. Help is on the way.

115
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,802
Thank you, ma'am.

116
00:06:33,268 --> 00:06:35,270
[engine clicking softly]

117
00:06:57,334 --> 00:06:59,336
[typing rapidly]

118
00:07:00,337 --> 00:07:01,922
[pen clicks]

119
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:06,300
Please have a seat.

120
00:07:06,301 --> 00:07:08,303
Your appointment's
not for another hour.

121
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:19,439
[scoffs softly]

122
00:07:25,821 --> 00:07:27,864
Excuse me.

123
00:07:27,865 --> 00:07:30,951
Are you the wife of the guy my
wife is having an affair with?

124
00:07:31,952 --> 00:07:34,288
We're not together anymore.

125
00:07:36,039 --> 00:07:39,168
- I'm Isabelle.
- Spence.

126
00:07:44,882 --> 00:07:47,508
Thanks, uh,

127
00:07:47,509 --> 00:07:51,137
for the heads-up...
at the barbecue.

128
00:07:51,138 --> 00:07:54,265
I'm not sure you should be
thanking me, but you're welcome.

129
00:07:54,266 --> 00:07:55,725
[door squeaks open]

130
00:07:55,726 --> 00:07:57,727
Oh, my God.

131
00:07:57,728 --> 00:08:00,438
Oh. I am so sorry.

132
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:02,315
This is something.

133
00:08:02,316 --> 00:08:03,774
Want to go get coffee?

134
00:08:03,775 --> 00:08:05,485
That might not be the best idea.

135
00:08:26,715 --> 00:08:29,133
You, uh... you look well.

136
00:08:29,134 --> 00:08:31,969
Thanks. I think
I'm having a good hair day.

137
00:08:31,970 --> 00:08:34,639
He vomited into it,
so I washed it.

138
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:36,557
Sorry.

139
00:08:36,558 --> 00:08:38,185
About what? My life?

140
00:08:39,228 --> 00:08:41,896
So, how'd you find Dr. Alison?

141
00:08:41,897 --> 00:08:44,941
She's okay. I...
I had some things

142
00:08:44,942 --> 00:08:48,861
I needed to get off my chest,
but I think I'm done now.

143
00:08:48,862 --> 00:08:51,490
- [Charlie cries]
- [phone buzzes]

144
00:08:53,617 --> 00:08:56,744
He keeps texting me
about Charlie.

145
00:08:56,745 --> 00:08:59,664
I wish he'd just get over
his guilt and leave us alone.

146
00:08:59,665 --> 00:09:01,582
Do you think they're in love?

147
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:04,919
I don't know.
And I don't care.

148
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,587
Why? Do you?

149
00:09:06,588 --> 00:09:11,592
If she was, I'd feel better
about her giving up on the plan.

150
00:09:11,593 --> 00:09:14,220
You've mentioned that before.
What was the plan?

151
00:09:14,221 --> 00:09:16,389
We were gonna have a baby.

152
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:18,599
And then, five more years,
a second.

153
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,434
And then, if I could manage,

154
00:09:20,435 --> 00:09:22,436
the house would be paid off
in 15 years.

155
00:09:22,437 --> 00:09:24,522
Then we'd go on a cruise,
see the glaciers, and...

156
00:09:24,523 --> 00:09:26,023
If they're still around.

157
00:09:26,024 --> 00:09:28,859
You know you can't really
plan life like that.

158
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:31,612
I guess not.

159
00:09:31,613 --> 00:09:33,657
I prefer to control
the controllable.

160
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:38,202
After you have your first kid,
you'll let go of some of that.

161
00:09:38,203 --> 00:09:40,329
You're right.

162
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:42,331
Maybe I won't have
children anymore.

163
00:09:42,332 --> 00:09:44,500
Hey, you never know.

164
00:09:44,501 --> 00:09:46,502
A goal without a plan
is just a wish.

165
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:48,754
Huh?

166
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:51,465
I wanted to get coffee because

167
00:09:51,466 --> 00:09:53,009
you're the only person

168
00:09:53,010 --> 00:09:54,760
who understands
what I'm going through.

169
00:09:54,761 --> 00:09:56,762
But at the same time, you know

170
00:09:56,763 --> 00:09:59,807
how completely ordinary
this situation is.

171
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:02,685
I was devastated
when it happened,

172
00:10:02,686 --> 00:10:07,690
but now I'm more...

173
00:10:07,691 --> 00:10:09,066
embarrassed.

174
00:10:09,067 --> 00:10:11,277
- You feel embarrassed?
- Yeah.

175
00:10:11,278 --> 00:10:14,947
Like I was robbed.

176
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:18,035
I don't want to feel
like this again.

177
00:10:20,829 --> 00:10:23,165
We should probably get going.

178
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,793
We got to go home.

179
00:10:31,006 --> 00:10:32,423
[Charlie crying]

180
00:10:32,424 --> 00:10:34,217
[clears throat softly]

181
00:10:38,597 --> 00:10:40,265
I'm glad we met.

182
00:10:42,601 --> 00:10:44,519
Why do you look so surprised?

183
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:49,357
I can't remember the last time
someone was glad to have met me.

184
00:10:49,358 --> 00:10:52,360
We're not them.

185
00:10:52,361 --> 00:10:54,779
At least we have that.

186
00:10:54,780 --> 00:10:56,656
Take care of yourself.

187
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:01,161
[Charlie fussing]

188
00:11:17,886 --> 00:11:19,596
Hmm.

189
00:11:23,642 --> 00:11:26,268
[Adam] Okay, Boyles,
your profile's set up.

190
00:11:26,269 --> 00:11:27,603
Just click on who you like.

191
00:11:27,604 --> 00:11:29,146
You make it sound so easy.

192
00:11:29,147 --> 00:11:31,399
[Adam] Give it a try.

193
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,318
Um...

194
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:35,653
[♪ Gold Star:
"San Francisco Good Times"]

195
00:11:35,654 --> 00:11:37,239
Hmm?

196
00:11:38,281 --> 00:11:39,866
Uh...

197
00:11:42,202 --> 00:11:44,413
[both chuckling]

198
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:51,168
Oh, all right. Uh, now what?

199
00:11:51,169 --> 00:11:52,211
Man, you write her.

200
00:11:52,212 --> 00:11:54,631
And if you hit it off,
you meet up.

201
00:11:56,967 --> 00:12:00,804
[indistinct voices in distance]

202
00:12:01,847 --> 00:12:03,849
[siren wailing in distance]

203
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:27,705
- So we agree?
- Definitely.

204
00:12:27,706 --> 00:12:30,040
This is definitely not a date.

205
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:32,376
I saw your profile...

206
00:12:32,377 --> 00:12:35,588
And it... it would have been
rude not to message.

207
00:12:35,589 --> 00:12:37,423
Exactly.

208
00:12:37,424 --> 00:12:40,176
It's my first night out
in a while.

209
00:12:40,177 --> 00:12:42,304
Mine, too.

210
00:12:50,395 --> 00:12:52,396
Do you know...
do you know what you want?

211
00:12:52,397 --> 00:12:55,816
Hey, you mentioned
you lost power after the storm.

212
00:12:55,817 --> 00:12:57,735
Yeah. And then
when the power came back,

213
00:12:57,736 --> 00:12:59,778
I couldn't get
some of my lights working.

214
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:01,656
I bet I can fix that for you.

215
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:06,494
Right now?

216
00:13:06,495 --> 00:13:08,120
We don't have to...

217
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:09,581
Okay.

218
00:13:12,834 --> 00:13:15,420
[speaking indistinctly]

219
00:13:19,674 --> 00:13:21,718
[chuckles] Yeah.
Let's get out of here.

220
00:13:28,058 --> 00:13:30,142
- [clicks]
- No.

221
00:13:30,143 --> 00:13:31,810
How about now?

222
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,396
No.

223
00:13:34,397 --> 00:13:37,484
Yes! [laughs]

224
00:13:47,577 --> 00:13:48,995
Hey.

225
00:13:50,163 --> 00:13:51,873
Since you didn't get any dinner.

226
00:14:00,298 --> 00:14:01,883
[door closes]

227
00:14:06,346 --> 00:14:08,806
I can't believe
you finally hung the curtains.

228
00:14:08,807 --> 00:14:10,432
Did Nick help you?

229
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:12,643
Definitely not.

230
00:14:12,644 --> 00:14:15,062
I have a friend.

231
00:14:15,063 --> 00:14:16,981
It's not that military guy
from therapy.

232
00:14:16,982 --> 00:14:20,359
Girl, that is so weird.
Wasn't he married to...

233
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:22,695
Yeah, you don't need
to remind me about his ex.

234
00:14:22,696 --> 00:14:25,030
So what, he's kind of, like,
a handyman with benefits?

235
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:26,991
We haven't actually...

236
00:14:26,992 --> 00:14:27,992
We're...

237
00:14:27,993 --> 00:14:29,578
we're friends.

238
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:33,581
I know it hasn't been easy
for you, with Charlie...

239
00:14:33,582 --> 00:14:35,416
You have no idea.

240
00:14:35,417 --> 00:14:37,751
But you should not lead a guy on

241
00:14:37,752 --> 00:14:39,795
because you want
your tiles re-grouted.

242
00:14:39,796 --> 00:14:42,798
Maybe I want a man
to re-grout my tiles.

243
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:44,925
[laughs]

244
00:14:44,926 --> 00:14:46,927
Have you always been this handy?

245
00:14:46,928 --> 00:14:48,596
No way.

246
00:14:48,597 --> 00:14:50,806
When I, uh,
got back from the Marines,

247
00:14:50,807 --> 00:14:52,766
I hadn't lived in a house
in a while.

248
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,311
You want to do it?

249
00:14:58,440 --> 00:15:00,774
Just run it slowly.

250
00:15:00,775 --> 00:15:02,318
[Isabelle] So,
when did that change?

251
00:15:02,319 --> 00:15:07,740
I threw myself into becoming
the best solider that I could.

252
00:15:07,741 --> 00:15:09,533
Until I wasn't
a solider anymore.

253
00:15:09,534 --> 00:15:11,368
And then when I got married,

254
00:15:11,369 --> 00:15:12,828
I wanted to be
the best husband I could be.

255
00:15:12,829 --> 00:15:14,538
And that includes
teaching yourself

256
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:16,541
electrical work and plumbing?

257
00:15:18,043 --> 00:15:20,086
Okay, bring it up.

258
00:15:21,379 --> 00:15:23,423
- Oh! I made that.
- [Spence laughs]

259
00:15:24,466 --> 00:15:27,009
And now...

260
00:15:27,010 --> 00:15:29,262
it is gone.

261
00:15:38,438 --> 00:15:40,774
You need a haircut.

262
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:47,363
Hey.

263
00:15:47,364 --> 00:15:48,947
Where are you?

264
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,825
Oh. Sorry.

265
00:15:53,662 --> 00:15:56,330
I wouldn't call myself
a creative person,

266
00:15:56,331 --> 00:15:59,334
but sometimes my mind
takes me places.

267
00:16:00,669 --> 00:16:03,087
Bad places?

268
00:16:03,088 --> 00:16:04,296
Not always.

269
00:16:04,297 --> 00:16:05,965
But sometimes.

270
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:12,179
How much experience
do you have up there?

271
00:16:12,180 --> 00:16:14,598
I've cut Charlie's hair
his whole life.

272
00:16:14,599 --> 00:16:16,601
He's never complained.

273
00:16:20,021 --> 00:16:23,233
I wanted to do something nice
for you, for once.

274
00:16:25,276 --> 00:16:28,445
I like making your life better.

275
00:16:28,446 --> 00:16:30,239
I mean...

276
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:32,075
I like trying.

277
00:16:38,415 --> 00:16:40,541
Do you want to go to d-dinner?

278
00:16:40,542 --> 00:16:41,750
I mean, like, a real...

279
00:16:41,751 --> 00:16:43,503
Yes.

280
00:16:50,677 --> 00:16:52,637
♪ ♪

281
00:16:55,557 --> 00:16:57,559
[ringtone playing]

282
00:17:00,854 --> 00:17:02,730
Oh, hey.

283
00:17:02,731 --> 00:17:06,400
- [Charlie crying]
- Hey. I'm sorry to do this
last-minute, but Charlie's sick.

284
00:17:06,401 --> 00:17:07,818
What?

285
00:17:07,819 --> 00:17:09,862
His fever won't break.

286
00:17:09,863 --> 00:17:12,364
I've been trying all day.

287
00:17:12,365 --> 00:17:13,991
Can I bring you anything?

288
00:17:13,992 --> 00:17:16,201
Nope.
We have everything we need.

289
00:17:16,202 --> 00:17:19,204
- I could take you
to the hospital.
- No, we're really fine.

290
00:17:19,205 --> 00:17:21,415
I just can't leave him
with a sitter like this.

291
00:17:21,416 --> 00:17:23,459
- Oh. Okay.
- I'm so sorry.

292
00:17:23,460 --> 00:17:24,752
Um...

293
00:17:24,753 --> 00:17:26,462
No, no.
Please don't worry about me.

294
00:17:26,463 --> 00:17:29,132
- Okay. Rain check?
- Rain check.

295
00:17:39,976 --> 00:17:42,395
[over speakers] Avery,
you have a call on line four.

296
00:17:51,821 --> 00:17:53,614
Spence.

297
00:17:53,615 --> 00:17:55,783
- It's, uh...
- I know who you are.

298
00:17:55,784 --> 00:17:57,075
Yeah, uh, sorry,

299
00:17:57,076 --> 00:17:59,077
I'll-I'll get out of your way
in a minute.

300
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:01,079
I... don't know what to get.

301
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,873
Are you asking my advice?

302
00:18:02,874 --> 00:18:04,249
No.

303
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:06,293
No, sorry, man.
My-my kid is sick.

304
00:18:06,294 --> 00:18:07,503
I'm sorry to hear that.

305
00:18:07,504 --> 00:18:09,838
Yeah. I mean,
his fever is sky-high.

306
00:18:09,839 --> 00:18:11,423
I-I wanted to take him
to the doctor,

307
00:18:11,424 --> 00:18:13,383
but his mother didn't want
to drag him to the ER

308
00:18:13,384 --> 00:18:14,802
and get stuck waiting there.

309
00:18:14,803 --> 00:18:16,386
She wants him to rest,

310
00:18:16,387 --> 00:18:18,597
see his regular pediatrician
in the morning, and...

311
00:18:18,598 --> 00:18:21,099
- I take it you don't agree?
- [sighs] I don't know.

312
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:23,393
I wanted to take him in
and make sure he's okay,

313
00:18:23,394 --> 00:18:25,187
but she's the mother, right?

314
00:18:25,188 --> 00:18:26,815
She knows best.

315
00:18:28,858 --> 00:18:30,150
Oh, God, I...

316
00:18:30,151 --> 00:18:32,152
can't believe
I'm unloading on you.

317
00:18:32,153 --> 00:18:33,570
You must hate me.

318
00:18:33,571 --> 00:18:35,615
That's a reasonable assumption.

319
00:18:42,038 --> 00:18:43,747
Um...

320
00:18:43,748 --> 00:18:45,415
are we okay?

321
00:18:45,416 --> 00:18:47,793
What do you mean, "Are we okay?"

322
00:18:47,794 --> 00:18:49,795
I'm not with Jeannie anymore.

323
00:18:49,796 --> 00:18:52,256
Is that supposed
to make me feel better?

324
00:18:52,257 --> 00:18:54,633
I don't know.

325
00:18:54,634 --> 00:18:58,637
Well, hey, man, not tonight,
obviously, but...

326
00:18:58,638 --> 00:19:02,267
let me know if you want to get
a beer and talk about it.

327
00:19:04,978 --> 00:19:06,980
♪ ♪

328
00:19:25,582 --> 00:19:27,249
[distorted, echoing explosion]

329
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:31,503
[muted, distorted voices
shouting]

330
00:19:31,504 --> 00:19:34,756
[distorted, echoing explosion]

331
00:19:34,757 --> 00:19:36,466
[muted, distorted voices
shouting]

332
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:39,929
[distorted, echoing explosion]

333
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:43,807
[Nick] Hey, hey, please don't...

334
00:19:43,808 --> 00:19:47,770
please, don't, don't, don't,
don't, please, please don't.

335
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:52,733
[amplified heartbeat]

336
00:19:52,734 --> 00:19:55,777
Hey, man, now we're okay.

337
00:19:55,778 --> 00:19:56,988
[echoing pop]

338
00:19:58,865 --> 00:20:00,240
Sorry.

339
00:20:00,241 --> 00:20:02,367
It was a stupid idea.

340
00:20:02,368 --> 00:20:04,662
Anyway, have a good night.

341
00:20:06,706 --> 00:20:07,999
Hey.

342
00:20:10,168 --> 00:20:13,211
You need to get Isabelle to let
you take Charlie to the ER.

343
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:14,880
You know my son's name?

344
00:20:14,881 --> 00:20:16,381
Don't let whatever's going on

345
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:19,134
between you and her
cloud your judgement.

346
00:20:19,135 --> 00:20:21,137
You're his father.

347
00:20:28,269 --> 00:20:31,355
[rhythmic beeping]

348
00:20:31,356 --> 00:20:33,816
- [beeping]
- [whooshing]

349
00:20:44,035 --> 00:20:45,535
Thanks for coming.

350
00:20:45,536 --> 00:20:47,538
Yeah.

351
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:59,049
It was meningitis.

352
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:01,176
That's crazy.

353
00:21:01,177 --> 00:21:02,803
I thought I knew best.

354
00:21:02,804 --> 00:21:05,847
I thought
I could do this on my own.

355
00:21:05,848 --> 00:21:07,265
Well, you were never
on your own.

356
00:21:07,266 --> 00:21:09,142
- I was there... No.
- Nick is, uh...

357
00:21:09,143 --> 00:21:10,560
Go on.

358
00:21:10,561 --> 00:21:13,313
Nick insisted that
we bring Charlie to the ER.

359
00:21:13,314 --> 00:21:16,274
It was like
he was a different man.

360
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:18,318
[crying]
He could have died,

361
00:21:18,319 --> 00:21:20,404
and it would have been my fault.

362
00:21:20,405 --> 00:21:23,699
My whole world would have
been over in an instant.

363
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:25,492
[sniffles]

364
00:21:25,493 --> 00:21:30,163
You can't...
you can't plan anything.

365
00:21:30,164 --> 00:21:31,832
Do you understand me?

366
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:35,168
Life cannot be planned.

367
00:21:35,169 --> 00:21:37,796
[sighs]

368
00:21:37,797 --> 00:21:40,133
Sorry. What were you gonna say?

369
00:21:41,509 --> 00:21:43,678
No. Uh...

370
00:21:47,056 --> 00:21:49,099
It sounds like he's finally

371
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:51,393
stepping into his role
as a father.

372
00:21:51,394 --> 00:21:54,062
Mm.

373
00:21:54,063 --> 00:21:56,065
Do you want to head back?

374
00:22:02,113 --> 00:22:04,281
- [rhythmic beeping]
- [whooshing]

375
00:22:04,282 --> 00:22:06,658
Look.

376
00:22:06,659 --> 00:22:08,661
I think he's smiling.

377
00:22:36,397 --> 00:22:38,482
[line ringing]

378
00:22:38,483 --> 00:22:43,987
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh,
ooh-ooh, ooh ♪

379
00:22:43,988 --> 00:22:47,324
♪ Now you know
who you're talking to ♪

380
00:22:47,325 --> 00:22:49,409
♪ You know I'm not a liar ♪

381
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:52,662
♪ I tore my pants
and learned to dance ♪

382
00:22:52,663 --> 00:22:55,165
♪ On love and razor wire ♪

383
00:22:55,166 --> 00:22:59,419
♪ I learned to keep on moving
when the flames ♪

384
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:02,547
♪ Were getting higher ♪

385
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:04,758
♪ When the devil's stuck ♪

386
00:23:04,759 --> 00:23:08,346
♪ And you keep walking
through the fire ♪

387
00:23:10,139 --> 00:23:12,516
♪ And I made friends
with the monsters ♪

388
00:23:12,517 --> 00:23:15,769
♪ Growling underneath my bed ♪

389
00:23:15,770 --> 00:23:21,650
♪ I held a ball and invited
all the voices in my head ♪

390
00:23:21,651 --> 00:23:28,657
♪ I heard the traffic humming
and I thought it was a choir ♪

391
00:23:28,658 --> 00:23:31,243
♪ Singing
when the devil's stuck ♪

392
00:23:31,244 --> 00:23:34,914
♪ And you keep walking
through the fire ♪

393
00:23:39,210 --> 00:23:45,090
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh, ooh ♪

394
00:23:45,091 --> 00:23:47,092
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh,
ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

395
00:23:47,093 --> 00:23:50,762
♪ Ooh, ooh,
ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

396
00:23:50,763 --> 00:23:54,641
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh, ooh...

397
00:23:54,642 --> 00:23:57,602
I wasn't sure if you'd show up.

398
00:23:57,603 --> 00:23:59,437
I'm sorry I didn't
answer your messages.

399
00:23:59,438 --> 00:24:01,439
Why didn't you?

400
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:03,733
Can we talk about that night?

401
00:24:03,734 --> 00:24:06,112
You told me you were going
to kill yourself.

402
00:24:07,822 --> 00:24:11,408
[Spence] That night
I managed to convince myself

403
00:24:11,409 --> 00:24:13,660
that things would be easier
if I wasn't around anymore.

404
00:24:13,661 --> 00:24:15,204
[Jeannie] You scared me.

405
00:24:16,622 --> 00:24:18,957
[Spence] I think I meant to.

406
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:21,501
I'm sorry.

407
00:24:21,502 --> 00:24:27,215
After you left,
I... kind of lost my purpose.

408
00:24:27,216 --> 00:24:30,343
Don't you think
that was part of the problem?

409
00:24:30,344 --> 00:24:31,970
I'm not a mission.

410
00:24:31,971 --> 00:24:33,890
You were to me.

411
00:24:39,478 --> 00:24:41,563
Are you zoning out right now?

412
00:24:41,564 --> 00:24:44,025
Are you even listening?

413
00:24:46,777 --> 00:24:48,779
I want you to be happy.

414
00:24:51,199 --> 00:24:54,242
I want you to be happy, too.

415
00:24:54,243 --> 00:24:56,787
Okay? Please?

416
00:24:59,207 --> 00:25:01,333
Jeannie?

417
00:25:01,334 --> 00:25:03,877
I'll sign the papers, okay?

418
00:25:03,878 --> 00:25:05,880
Thank you.

419
00:25:08,925 --> 00:25:13,887
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

420
00:25:13,888 --> 00:25:17,140
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh,
ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

421
00:25:17,141 --> 00:25:19,393
Oh.

422
00:25:21,312 --> 00:25:25,982
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh, ooh ♪

423
00:25:25,983 --> 00:25:28,526
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh,
ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

424
00:25:28,527 --> 00:25:31,906
♪ Ooh, ooh,
ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh ♪♪

425
00:25:37,453 --> 00:25:39,455
[sniffles]

426
00:25:53,511 --> 00:25:55,513
[indistinct crowd chatter]

427
00:26:04,981 --> 00:26:06,982
- Hey, stranger.
- Hi.

428
00:26:06,983 --> 00:26:08,901
- It's good to see you.
- You as well.

429
00:26:11,654 --> 00:26:14,197
That's Nick's new girlfriend.

430
00:26:14,198 --> 00:26:16,574
She's nice, actually.

431
00:26:16,575 --> 00:26:18,326
I mean, she's fine.

432
00:26:18,327 --> 00:26:20,078
I thought
you two were back together.

433
00:26:20,079 --> 00:26:24,249
No. I deserve better
than that, don't I?

434
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:26,335
Here's my dude.

435
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:37,929
Happy birthday, Charlie.

436
00:26:37,930 --> 00:26:39,932
Ah. What is that?

437
00:26:41,934 --> 00:26:43,935
Is that why you disappeared?

438
00:26:43,936 --> 00:26:46,438
I didn't want to get in the way.

439
00:26:46,439 --> 00:26:48,565
That's silly.

440
00:26:48,566 --> 00:26:50,358
You good?

441
00:26:50,359 --> 00:26:52,569
I'm doing the best I can.

442
00:26:52,570 --> 00:26:54,154
According to plan?

443
00:26:54,155 --> 00:26:56,823
Ah, there is no plan.

444
00:26:56,824 --> 00:26:58,908
- [Spence laughs]
- [Brynn] Hey.

445
00:26:58,909 --> 00:27:00,243
Should we do the cake soon?

446
00:27:00,244 --> 00:27:01,619
Just a sec.

447
00:27:01,620 --> 00:27:03,622
Katie?

448
00:27:06,167 --> 00:27:07,584
- Hi, Katie.
- [Katie gasps, babbles]

449
00:27:07,585 --> 00:27:10,754
Can I, uh, help with anything?

450
00:27:10,755 --> 00:27:12,380
Uh, yes, actually.

451
00:27:12,381 --> 00:27:14,049
I could use a night out
with a grownup.

452
00:27:14,050 --> 00:27:15,925
Oh.

453
00:27:15,926 --> 00:27:17,635
Please don't feel obligated.

454
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:20,388
Thanks. I won't.
So, Friday?

455
00:27:20,389 --> 00:27:22,390
Yeah?

456
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:25,685
Okay, it's a plan.

457
00:27:25,686 --> 00:27:28,356
Was that a joke?

458
00:27:32,234 --> 00:27:34,778
Hey, birthday boy.

459
00:27:34,779 --> 00:27:37,030
Okay, let's sing.

460
00:27:37,031 --> 00:27:40,950
Mm. One, two, three.

461
00:27:40,951 --> 00:27:44,496
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

462
00:27:44,497 --> 00:27:47,707
♪ Happy birthday
